<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: BASS CREATE OWN STORM AT LAKES CASTAIC, CASITAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 There was no calm before Monday's storm at Lake Castaic and Lake Casitas, as 
trophy-sized largemouth bass went on a feeding spree in the days leading up to 
the rain. 
</P>
<P>
 At Casitas in Ventura County, Marlin Spenser of Santa Barbara used a Worm King 
lure to catch a 15-pound 4-ounce bass and Bill Jordan of Santa Paula used 
crawfish to catch a 12-8 and an 8-5 bass. At Castaic in Los Angeles County, 
Eric Stepanek of Newhall and Ray Marrill of Granada Hills used live shad to 
catch, among several others, a nine-pound bass, two 8-0s and a 7-0. All fish 
were released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
