<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; CHARGING CALL ALLOWS PALMDALE TO ESCAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Littlerock High, the fourth-place team in the Golden League, thought it had 
upset The Times' third-ranked team on its home floor Tuesday night, but a 
charging call with one second left wiped out the would-be winning basket and 
allowed Palmdale to beat the Lobos, 58-56. 
</P>
<P>
 Palmdale (16-3, 10-0 in Golden League play) took a 57-56 lead when Maurice 
Wright made a 10-foot baseline jump shot. Littlerock (8-10, 4-6) rushed the 
ball up the floor and John George, who scored 18 points, made a layup with one 
second left. However, James Jefferson was called for an offensive foul after he 
passed to George. 
</P>
<P>
 In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
 Highland 58, Antelope Valley 56 -- Highland's Pharoah Davis scored 27 points 
before fouling out with two minutes to play in the Golden League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Adam O'Leno scored from underneath to break a 54-54 tie with 48 seconds left 
and Jamal Dedeaux (21 points) made two free throws to give the Bulldogs (12-6, 
7-3) a four-point lead with 17 seconds remaining. 
</P>
<P>
 Arcadia 40, Hoover 37 -- Raffie Hajjar's basket with 40 seconds left gave 
Arcadia its first lead in the Pacific League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale 67, Pasadena 45 -- The Dynamiters (16-5, 4-1) held Pasadena (12-7, 
4-2) to 17 points in the second half of a Pacific League game. Glendale was led 
by Manny Gonzalez (18 points), James Fuller (15) and David Elliott (13). 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas 90, Viewpoint 61 -- Nick Alexander had 26 points and 13 rebounds and 
Ryan Coleman added eight assists for the Coyotes (8-9) in a nonleague game. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 54, Santa Paula 50 -- Keith Linton's jumper with three seconds to 
play gave Moorpark a Frontier League victory. MEN 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 94, CS San Bernardino 76 -- Andy Thompson scored 22 points to 
lead the Mustangs (19-3) to a nonconference victory at Newhall. Emeka Okenwa 
had 14 rebounds for The Master's. GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
 Royal 54, Thousand Oaks 42 -- Tawnee Cooper scored 17 points to lead the 
Highlanders (12-3, 5-2) in a Marmonte League game. Paula Getty-Shear said the 
victory was the Highlanders' first over the Lancers (13-6, 5-3) in her six 
years at Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 Buena 56, Rio Mesa 34 -- Eboni Conley scored 20 points to lead the Bulldogs 
(14-1, 8-0) to a Channel League victory. Mikko Giordano added 11 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park 62, La Reina 52 -- Alexa Valavanis had eight points, 10 rebounds, six 
steals and six assists for the Eagles (14-5, 4-1) to a Tri-Valley League 
victory. Alicia Valavanis added 20 points for Oak Park. WOMEN 
</P>
<P>
 Claremont-Mudd 81, Cal Lutheran 62 -- Cal Lutheran held a three-point lead at 
the half, but surrendered 49 second-half points in a Southern California 
Intercollegiate Athletic Conference game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
