COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tes Whitlock 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Basketball / Guard 
</P>
<P>
 Whitlock came to Saddleback as a proven offensive player.He averaged 33.5 
points as a senior at Loara High School and earned a scholarship to Arizona 
State. But things didn't work out, and he returned to enroll at Saddleback. 
Whitlock has shown his typical offensive skills, averaging a team-high 19 
points. He scored 29 points, including Saddleback's first 16, in the second 
half of the Gauchos' 83-70 victory over Golden West last Wednesday. He came 
back to score 25 as Saddleback beat Orange Coast, 70-52, Friday. 
</P>
