<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; ZITTERKOPF PACES SCC WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jamie Zitterkopf scored 20 points to help Southern California College to a 
79-60 victory over Occidental in a nonconference women's basketball game 
Tuesday at Occidental. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the 14th victory in 15 games for Southern California College (16-4), 
which had its 13-game winning streak stopped in a 62-50 loss to Fresno Pacific 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanja SimiDzija added 17 for Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific 80, Concordia 77 -- Jessica Opfar made three free throws in the 
final six seconds for host Azusa Pacific (13-7, 2-2). Opfar went up for a shot 
with six seconds left and was fouled by Gitte Mejer. She made one of two free 
throws to give Azusa Pacific a 78-77 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 She then got a steal and was fouled again with three seconds left. She made 
both free throws to finish with 22 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Mejer, who fouled out when she fouled Opfar, had a game-high 31 points. She 
has scored 132 points in her last three games. Julie Workman added 21 for 
Concordia (10-8, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Azusa Pacific 97, Concordia 71 -- Raymond Tuh had 28 points, making 11 of 14 
shots from the field, for host Azusa Pacific (19-2, 4-0), the ninth-ranked team 
in the NAIA national poll. Craig Martin had 19 for Concordia (13-7, 2-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Christian 106, California Christian 76 -- Charles Ross scored a 
game-high 35 points, Chuck Henderson added 17, Ruxton Schmietenknop had 15 and 
Eric Bajus finished with 14 for Pacific Christian (12-13). 
</P>
