<TEXT>
<P>
 After squandering a 12-point lead in the fourth quarter, Mater Dei came back 
to beat San Clemente, 76-67, in overtime in a South Coast League girls' 
basketball game Tuesday at San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente outscored Mater Dei, 27-15, in the fourth quarter but was 
outscored, 11-2, in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 Tina Afan scored 19 points and Melody Peterson had 17 -- including 13 after 
halftime -- for Mater Dei (15-4, 6-0 in league), the fourth-ranked team in 
Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 San Clemente's Jenny Geminert had a rebound basket as time expired in 
regulation to force overtime. Michelle Macintyre scored 31 points for the 
ninth-ranked Tritons (14-5, 4-2). 
