<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' SOCCER ROUNDUP; MARINA'S BENSON GETS VICTORY, AND A PARTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Top-ranked Marina dominated eighth-ranked Ocean View everywhere in the first 
half, except the scoreboard. 
</P>
<P>
 "It got sort of frustrating," Marina midfielder Jenny Benson said. "You only 
get so many opportunities." 
</P>
<P>
 But Benson didn't let her opportunity pass in the second half as she whistled 
a wide-open shot past Ocean View goalkeeper Keri Lawson to give her team a 1-0 
victory in a Sunset League girls' soccer game Tuesday at Marina, and herself a 
present on her 16th birthday. 
</P>
<P>
 Afterward, Benson's teammates thanked her by giving her a birthday hat and 
singing happy birthday. 
</P>
<P>
 "It was nice to score a goal on my birthday," she said. "It was a set-piece, 
and I was wide open." 
</P>
<P>
 Benson was actually denied on her first shot, but the rebound came back to 
her. She didn't miss again and scored her 10th goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina (19-0-1, 6-0-1 in league) outshot Ocean View, 13-1, in the first half 
and, 20-4, in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 "We always have trouble with them," Benson said. "We just needed to hang 
tough." 
</P>
<P>
 After Benson scored, Ocean View (12-7-2, 3-3-1) had one more chance to score, 
but Kimberly Engesser's shot was deflected off the crossbar by Marina 
goalkeeper Jennifer Simmons with 10 minutes left. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina extended its unbeaten streak to 30 games. 
</P>
<P>
 In other Sunset League games: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 2, Huntington Beach 0 -- Second-ranked Edison (18-3-2, 6-1) remained a 
half-game behind Marina. Nicole Price and Erin Bailey scored for the Chargers. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Olympic League: 
</P>
<P>
 Whittier Christian 4, Brethren Christian 4 -- Sabrina Shannon scored two goals 
for Whittier Christian (4-8-2, 1-5-2) and Joy Pelletier scored two for Brethren 
Christian (7-6-2, 4-2-2).  
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 5, Western 2 -- Elida O'Campo scored two goals, and Christina Ramirez, 
Kellie Fernandez and Elide O'Campo each added one to lead Anaheim (6-10, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 5, Magnolia 0 -- Jennifer Overholtzer, Renata Soqui and Angie 
Smith scored in the first half for host Brea-Olinda (7-6-3, 5-0-1). Juli Evers 
and Amy Alexander scored second-half goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 0, Savanna 0 -- Valencia (6-6-5, 3-0-3) still hasn't been scored on 
in league play, but failed to get a victory as Savanna's Rene Miller recorded 
20 saves. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
