<TEXT>
<P>
 Atty. Gen. Janet Reno said the Justice Department will conduct a civil rights 
investigation of a Jewish scholar's slaying during the 1991 Crown Heights 
riots.Reno made the decision after hearing pleas from lawmakers and Brooklyn 
Dist. Atty. Charles J. Hynes, whose office was criticized after a state jury 
acquitted the only defendant charged in the case. Three days of violence 
erupted after a car in the motorcade of a Jewish religious leader jumped a curb 
and killed a 7-year-old black boy. Yankel Rosenbaum, a Hasidic scholar from 
Australia, was later fatally stabbed by a group of blacks. 
