 House Minority Leader Robert H. Michel pulled back from plans to seek a 
special committee to investigate President Clinton's business dealings in 
Arkansas.The Illinois Republican cited the appointment of a special counsel for 
his change of mind. He urged that regular House committees conduct hearings on 
