<P>
VICTOR LOMBARDO; BANDLEADER, PERFORMED WITH ROYAL CANADIANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Victor Lombardo, 82, youngest brother of musician Guy Lombardo and a 
bandleader in his own right. A native of London, Canada, the younger Lombardo 
was a featured performer in hundreds of recordings and musical films in the 
1930s and 1940s.He was the saxophone soloist in his brother's Royal Canadians 
and briefly took over the band's direction after Guy died in 1977. Bearing a 
close resemblance to his brother, Victor Lombardo soothed television viewers by 
fronting the Canadians at their annual appearance at New York's Waldorf Astoria 
Hotel for the 1977 New Year's Eve. But Victor soon left over "little 
differences" with another brother, Lebert, and formed his own band. On Saturday 
in Boca Raton, Fla., of complications of asthma. 
