<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: CENTRAL; STUDENT SAFETY TOPIC OF FAMILY PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Walton Intermediate School will host a safety forum for parents and students 
on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 During the meeting, which starts at 7 p.m., police and school officials will 
discuss strategies for keeping children safe, provide security tips and answer 
questions from the audience, said Alan Trudell, spokesman for the Garden Grove 
Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum is sponsored by Walton Intermediate PTA, and free child care will be 
provided. For guests who speak Spanish, Korean or Vietnamese, translators will 
be provided, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The event is free and open to the public, and refreshments will be provided. 
The forum will be held at the multipurpose room at Walton, 12821 Buaro St. 
</P>
<P>
 The Garden Grove School District serves most of Garden Grove, and portions of 
Santa Ana, Anaheim, Westminster, Cypress, Stanton and Fountain Valley. JON 
NALICK 
</P>
