<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SADDLEBACK/SOUTH BEACH; MISSION VIEJO; SADDLEBACK COLLEGE 
NAMES PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ned Doffoney, academic affairs vice president of Los Angeles City College, has 
been named president of Saddleback College. 
</P>
<P>
 Doffoney, 43, said he was notified of the selection Tuesday morning and plans 
to assume his new job on March 7. 
</P>
<P>
 The hiring of Doffoney, an African American, also brings a racial minority to 
the top position of a college that has been beset with racial problems in the 
last year, including reported threats against black students and the 
circulation of racist flyers. 
</P>
<P>
 Doffoney has been in his current position at LACC since 1990. He previously 
was academic affairs vice president and dean of academic affairs at Los Angeles 
Southwest College, assistant dean of admissions and records at Los Angeles 
Trade-Technical College, and financial aid and affirmative action director at 
Lassen College in Susanville. RICHARD CORE 
</P>
</TEXT>
