<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN KILLED IN FIERY CAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man driving a stolen car ran a traffic light Tuesday, lost control and 
smashed into a parked car that caught fire and killed the occupant, the Los 
Angeles Police Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters who arrived at the crash scene at 5:45 p.m. did not know there 
was anyone in the car until they extinguished the fire, said Police Sgt. Ron 
Ryan of the Valley Traffic Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the stolen car, whose identity was not available, was treated 
for chest cuts at North Hollywood Medical Center, Ryan said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred near the corner of Lankershim Boulevard and Hesby 
Street, near the dead man's home, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver will probably be charged with felony manslaughter, Ryan said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
