Minor 59% 39% Major 29% 6% Unlivable 1% 2% * 
</P>
<P>
 * Fully 42% of the people who lived 5 miles or less from the epicenter had 
major damage, compared with 24% of those 6-10 miles away and 18% of those in 
the 11-20 mile zone. 
</P>
<P>
 * Nearly 3 in 10 (28%) say they had earthquake insurance prior to the 
Northridge earthquake, up from 14% in the Valley before the 1987 Whittier 
quake. Only 12% intend to get earthquake insurance now, 42% still have no 
intention of getting insurance. 
</P>
<P>
