<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; 4 REAPPOINTED TO PLANNING BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After doing away with two of seven positions on the Planning Commission and 
restructuring the terms of the remaining five, the Oxnard City Council on 
Tuesday reappointed four of the current members. 
</P>
<P>
 Each council member went with past experience in selecting an appointee to the 
commission, which makes planning recommendations to the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Manuel F. Lopez chose Edward Castillo, Councilman Michael A. Plisky 
named Dale Dean, Councilman Andres Herrera selected Arthur Joe Lopez, and 
Councilman Bedford Pinkard chose Albert G. Duff. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Thomas E. Holden selected Sonny Okada, a former planning 
commissioner who applied for the job hours before Tuesday's council meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the restructuring ordinance approved last month, each planning 
commissioner will serve on the advisory panel for as long as the council member 
who made the appointment serves on the council. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan was criticized by several former commissioners. 
</P>
<P>
 "I didn't figure I would be (named) simply because I've come out against the 
restructuring," said Ralph Schumacher, one-time chairman of the Planning 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 "I also feel that if I was to serve as a commissioner, I would have to serve 
the people," Schumacher said. "I don't want to be politically attached to any 
council member." JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
