<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CASITAS SPRINGS; REPAIRS AFTER CRASH CLOSE HIGHWAY 
33 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 California 33 was closed at Casitas Springs for seven hours Tuesday as utility 
crews repaired power lines that were knocked down during a hit-and-run accident 
that sent two men to the hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Morning commuters between Ojai and Ventura were forced to detour around Oak 
View on Santa Ana Road. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 12:10 a.m. Tuesday when an unidentified driver 
lost control of his car and slammed into the utility pole. 
</P>
<P>
 The man fled the scene, leaving two injured passengers, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Juan Carlos Gomez Ortiz, 25, of Ojai, was taken to Ventura County Medical 
Center with moderate injuries. He was listed in good condition late Tuesday, a 
nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
 The second passenger, Javier Francisco Sanchez, 26, of Ojai was also taken to 
Ventura County Medical Center with injuries. A nursing supervisor said he was 
in satisfactory condition Tuesday evening. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP officials were still looking for the driver Tuesday night. He is wanted on 
suspicion of drunk driving and felony hit and run. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
