<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY: THOUSAND OAKS; MAN ARRESTED IN DEC. 31 ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies in Thousand Oaks have arrested a 27-year-old man on 
suspicion of sexually assaulting a 40-year-old woman in her motel room on New 
Year's Eve, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 William Franklin Goff was taken into custody Monday and booked into jail at 
the East County Sheriff's Station.He was released later that day on his promise 
to appear in Ventura County Municipal Court on Jan. 31. 
</P>
<P>
 The arrest came after the woman told sheriff's detectives that Goff sexually 
assaulted her inside her motel room after they had attended a party in Simi 
Valley on New Year's Eve. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman told deputies she had become intoxicated at the party and allowed 
Goff, with whom she was acquainted, to drive her back to her motel room in 
Thousand Oaks. She then asked him to leave and passed out on the bed. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the woman, she later discovered that Goff undressed her and 
sexually assaulted her while she was unconscious, sheriff's deputies said. 
JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
