<P>
 Spain Girds for General Strike: A conflict between the Socialist government 
and labor unions over measures to counter recession and rising unemployment 
will come to a head Thursday, when unions try to bring the country to a halt 
with a 24-hour general strike.At the heart of the dispute is a government bill 
to reform a rigid labor market. The government says the reforms, which make it 
easier for employers to hire and fire and encourage recruitment of apprentices, 
will give more people access to the labor market in a country where 23% of the 
work force is jobless. Unions say the reforms represent a direct attack on 
hard-won workers' rights and will undermine job security. 
</P>
