$23.875, mirroring a 19% drop in Mexico City trading. Dina said airline 
competition is reducing demand for buses in Mexico, crimping new orders. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: D.A. Campbell Co., Times wire services SPOTLIGHT: ZIMBABWE 
</P>
<P>
 President Robert Mugabe renounced communism two years ago in favor of an 
austerity program -- including cuts in subsidies, a devalued currency and cuts 
in the money supply. The reform program has created high unemployment. 
Inflation remains high because of government spending policies. 
</P>
<P>
 Sources: Bank of America, World Information Services 
