<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE; HYMAN CONSTRUCTION WINS CONTRACT TO EXPAND FLAMINGO IN 
LAS VEGAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Debora Vrana, Times correspondent 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 George Hyman Construction Co. in Irvine has won a $70-million contract to 
expand the Las Vegas Flamingo Hilton, a famous casino hotel built by gangster 
Benjamin (Bugsy) Siegel in 1946. 
</P>
<P>
 Workers in Hyman Construction's Irvine office will manage the 
600,000-square-foot expansion, which is to include a 28-story tower with 600 
rooms. The tower will connect to the existing hotel and encircle a large 
courtyard with pools, flamingo ponds and a wedding pavilion overlooking an 
18-foot waterfall. 
</P>
<P>
 The company has also won a $30-million contract from Hilton Grand Vacations 
Inc. for a new 340,000-square-foot time-share facility next to the Flamingo 
Hilton in Las Vegas. 
</P>
