charge of $3.2 million from an accounting change.As previously announced, the 
company changed its fiscal year end from Jan. 31 to Dec. 31. For the previous 
year ended Jan. 31, the company reported a profit of $15.4 million, or $1.45 a 
share. Sales increased to $557.9 million from $541.5 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
