<TEXT>
<P>
 Metalclad Corp.: The Newport Beach firm said Friday that it will not build a 
hazardous-waste treatment and landfill project near Guadalcazar, Mexico, until 
it receives full state and local government support. 
</P>
<P>
 Metalclad said the project has all permits and capital necessary to begin 
construction, but the company wanted to avoid potential criticism caused by 
inadvertently ignoring local customs. 
</P>
<P>
 Metalclad said it is providing information about the plant requested by the 
governor of the state, San Luis Potosi, and the city of Guadalcazar. 
