<P>
 Carl Karcher Enterprises Inc.: The restaurateur has been sued by a Ventura 
County couple who said the Anaheim company misled them about the viability of 
its restaurants three years ago when they agreed to purchase eight franchise 
locations in Central California for $4.4 million. The lawsuit, filed Monday in 
Orange County Superior Court, accuses Karcher Enterprises of fraud, violating 
state franchise investment regulations and of breaching its fiduciary duty to a 
franchisee. Plaintiffs Sabrina and Alexander Shin, who said the eight 
restaurants have yet to operate at a profit, have asked for restitution and an 
unspecified amount of damages. 
