<TEXT>
<P>
 InVitro International: The Irvine-based manufacturer of non-animal-test kits 
for testing corrosive materials said Monday that Canada's transportation 
department approved the firm's Corrositex, which is used to evaluate potential 
corrosion to the skin. Canada is the first country outside of the United States 
to formally approve the use of InVitro's Corrositex, its newest product, to 
test products entering its borders. InVitro stock closed at $4.75 on the Nasdaq 
market, up 50 cents from Monday. 
